		<p>
			Through the study of art history, we can learn about the different styles,
			techniques, and movements that have emerged over time, as well as the key
			figures who have shaped the course of art history. We can explore the ways
			in which art has been used to communicate ideas, tell stories, and
			challenge conventions, and we can appreciate the beauty and complexity of
			artworks from around the world.
		</p>
		<p>
			Whether you are an art lover, a student of history, or simply curious
			about the world around you, art history is a fascinating and rewarding
			subject to explore. So why not dive in and discover the incredible world
			of art history for yourself?
		</p>
		<SideBySide
			altText='Café Terrace at Night by Vincent Van Gogh'
			imgName='cafeterrace.jpg'
			needTextDescription
		>
			<p>
				One of the most exciting aspects of art history is the way in which it
				allows us to trace the evolution of artistic expression over time. By
				studying different periods and styles, <ExternalLink
					src='https://www.metmuseum.org/'
					title='we can see how artists have'
				/>

				responded to the social, political, and cultural context of their times,
				and how their work has both reflected and shaped these contexts. We can
				also see how artists have been influenced by one another, and how their
				ideas and techniques have been passed down from generation to
				generation.
			</p>
			<p>
				At the same time, art history also allows us to appreciate the unique
				qualities of individual artworks, and to understand the meanings and
				messages they convey. Whether we are looking at a painting, a sculpture,
				or a piece of architecture, we can explore the ways in which the artist
				has used form, color, composition, and other elements to create a
				powerful and evocative work of art. We can also consider the symbolism
				and cultural significance of these elements, and how they relate to the
				broader themes and ideas of the work.
			</p>
			<p>
				Finally, studying art history can also deepen our understanding of the
				world around us, and of ourselves as human beings. By exploring the
				diverse range of artistic traditions that have emerged throughout
				history, we can gain insights into the ways in which different cultures
				have sought to express their values, beliefs, and aspirations. We can
				also consider the role that art has played in shaping our own lives and
				identities, and in shaping the world we live in today.
			</p>
		</SideBySide>
